1
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:07,173
(Toshie) It’s tough! Maybe someone came who looked really dangerous.

2
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:08,299
(Tatsumi) Huh?

3
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:10,802
(Gouda) Bring out Kotaro!

4
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:13,513
(Goda) Where is it! ?

5
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:20,520
Call Kotaro Sensei

6
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:23,064
Ha, come back soon...

7
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:25,942
“You must never come back.”

8
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:28,111
(Sound of door opening) (Torataro) I'm back~

9
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:29,112
(sound of door closing)

10
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:34,826
(Torataro) Hey... huh...

11
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:38,079
What... What is it? What is it? Whoa, whoa...

12
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:40,707
- (Torataro) I'm sorry, I'm sorry - (Gouda) Torataro

13
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:43,585
Let's talk for a while

14
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:50,759
It's been an hour since we've been holed up together, just the two of us.

15
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,385
(Tatsumi) If it's a Kisei match or a Kiou match ⸺

16
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:55,597
This is a long thought that will take up a quarter of your time.

17
00:00:57,724 --> 00:00:58,975
Should I call the police?

18
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:01,895
It's your turn

19
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:04,355
Why me? Wait... why?

20
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:13,281
I'll be back again.

21
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:21,289
(Sound of door opening and closing)

22
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:22,373
(Rie) Hey, hey...

23
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,960
Huh? Are you okay? Nothing done? Yeah?

24
00:01:26,044 --> 00:01:27,837
Huh? Eh, wait... what are you talking about?

25
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:29,214
Because that terrible feeling⸺

26
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:30,840
No matter how you look at it, it's probably a thank you visit or something.

27
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:34,260
(Torataro) Ah... No, that's not it. It's a job request.

28
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:35,929
What crime was that person accused of?

29
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:38,348
(Rie) Theft? robbery? No, no way, another murder?

30
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:41,226
(Torataro) No, no, no, that's not it, it's a civil matter.

31
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:44,604
I have decided to file a civil lawsuit on your behalf.

32
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:46,147
Why did you accept it?

33
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:48,274
If by any chance I lose, it will be like before...

34
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:52,654
Even if it's cool, I won't lose!

35
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:55,782
yes

36
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,493
♪～

37
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:10,630
～♪

38
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:12,757
 (Rie) Fukuo Goda (Fukuo)

39
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:15,385
Ah, that mad dog-like man⸺

40
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:18,888
I'm not Kotaro-sensei's middle school classmate.

41
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,223
thank you

42
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:28,731
(Tatsumi) “Assuming there is no justifiable reason for refusing to renew the lease contract⸺”

43
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:32,443
“A lawsuit to confirm the status of the tenant”?

44
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:33,528
yes

45
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:37,073
Goda lives in a rented apartment in Koto Ward⸺

46
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:40,577
Last week, the landlord, Tetsuichi Ebihara, suddenly contacted me...

47
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:44,873
(Ebihara) Hey, the rental contract won't be renewed in six months, so please move out.

48
00:02:44,956 --> 00:02:47,125
I was told that my contract would not be renewed.

49
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,210
(Tatsumi) To have it withdrawn⸺

50
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:52,547
Does that mean you're filing a lawsuit against your landlord?

51
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,215
That mad dog⸺

52
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:56,718
Why did a classmate named Goda want to sue?

53
00:02:56,801 --> 00:03:01,181
Ah, no, it seems like Goda didn't have a trial in mind⸺

54
00:03:01,264 --> 00:03:04,517
I decided it would be better for me to go to court.

55
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:09,230
However, in the case of a rental apartment, the tenant has the right to rent...

56
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:11,858
Well, because I have the so-called right of residence⸺

57
00:03:11,941 --> 00:03:16,154
Even if you refuse renewal, you need a valid reason, right?

58
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:17,989
I asked Goda about that⸺

59
00:03:18,072 --> 00:03:20,992
Maybe it was because the landlord's dog ran away.

60
00:03:21,075 --> 00:03:22,368
dog?

61
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:23,953
(Torataro) Landlord Ebihara-san⸺

62
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:26,205
I live on the first floor of the same apartment as Goda⸺

63
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:28,458
I have a dog in my room⸺

64
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:31,502
Looks like someone let the dog escape...

65
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:34,214
Mr. Ebihara decided that the culprit was Goda⸺

66
00:03:34,297 --> 00:03:37,508
They say they won't renew the contract⸺

67
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:38,635
Goda himself...

68
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:41,721
…Is there any reason for that! There's no way a dog could escape.

69
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:43,723
(Rie) Actually, even if I let her escape⸺

70
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:46,184
He doesn't seem like the type to admit it honestly...

71
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:49,604
In addition to the dog, if there is rent arrears or trouble with the residents, etc.

72
00:03:49,687 --> 00:03:52,190
Rejection of renewal may be deemed unavoidable⸺

73
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:55,026
If you lose to a bad guy, won't there be some kind of resentment?

74
00:03:55,109 --> 00:04:00,365
This game may be the first off-board brawl.

75
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:06,579
It's up to you what you think about Goda, though.

76
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:08,247
I've already accepted your request⸺

77
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:11,501
I'll handle this lawsuit alone.

78
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:12,502
Huh?

79
00:04:17,048 --> 00:04:18,800
(Torataro) I'll go and ask.

80
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:26,057
(Torataro) Here?

81
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:30,186
(Suzuko) Look, don't fret anymore!

82
00:04:30,269 --> 00:04:33,982
...I'm going to post all of this by the end of today.

83
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:35,316
(Suzuko) It's already there...

84
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,943
-(Torataro) Um... -(Suzuko) Huh?

85
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,820
Did the dog run away?

86
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:42,824
-(Suzuko) That's right~ -(Torataro) Ah...

87
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:46,869
This person forgot to lock the room⸺

88
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:51,749
The defector in room 5 has escaped.

89
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:53,751
Poor Kotaro-chan

90
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,461
-(Torataro) Torataro? -(Suzuko) No, Kotaro.

91
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:56,796
(Kotaro) Kotaro... Kotaro?

92
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:58,631
Ah Kotaro

93
00:04:58,715 --> 00:04:59,882
(Suzuko) Yeah...

94
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,217
-(Torataro) Um... -(Suzuko) Yes.

95
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:03,511
This is the landlord, Mr. Ebihara, right?

96
00:05:03,594 --> 00:05:07,515
Could you please tell me more about the story of when the dog ran away?

97
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:08,641
(Suzuko) Ah...

98
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:16,024
Oh, that day I was weeding in the backyard⸺

99
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:18,484
I forgot to lock my room.

100
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:20,403
 (dog barking)

101
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:27,076
(sound of door opening)

102
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:31,414
Hey, what are you doing at someone's house?

103
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:35,126
-(Goda) It's nothing.-(Ebihara) Hey, just step away.

104
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,506
-(Ebihara) Hey! - (Goda) Oh?

105
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:42,341
-(Ebihara) Where did you go? - (Goda) Oh?

106
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:44,427
(Ebihara) You did something outrageous, give it back quickly!

107
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,804
(Goda) Don't be silly, I'm not doing anything!

108
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:47,805
(Ebihara) Put it back!

109
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:49,474
-(Goda) Oh? What! -(Ebihara) Give it back quickly!

110
00:05:49,557 --> 00:05:51,517
(Goda) I guess that's why you're not doing anything!

111
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:54,729
Hey, it's not a show!

112
00:05:55,396 --> 00:05:56,856
(Torataro) Well, you let the dog escape.

113
00:05:56,939 --> 00:05:58,524
You haven't actually seen it, have you?

114
00:05:58,608 --> 00:06:00,360
(Ebihara) No, I don't see anything⸺

115
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:03,321
He was in front of the room when Kotaro ran away.

116
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:05,490
Even before that, I often go to my room⸺

117
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:07,575
He's the one who's the voyeuristic one.

118
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:09,660
No, but there's no need to go out of your way to let the dog escape...

119
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:11,079
(Suzuko) Before too⸺

120
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:13,915
I was complaining about Kotaro⸺

121
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:16,167
I'm sure he did it out of anger.

122
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,920
Ah, you should kick me out quickly.

123
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:23,800
Yes, let's go next time... Kotaro-chan

124
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:25,635
Ah...

125
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:30,098
- (Ichikawa) What? Inquiry? -(Torataro) Yes.

126
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:32,225
(Ichikawa) Ask me anything about this apartment.

127
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,226
I'm pretty knowledgeable

128
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:34,519
Is it true?

129
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:37,063
What do you think of Goda-san's daily lifestyle?

130
00:06:37,146 --> 00:06:40,483
That person looks bad at first glance⸺

131
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,693
It seems like the monthly rent was paid properly.

132
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:44,362
Were there any delinquencies?

133
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:46,280
(Ichikawa) If you fall into arrears, it's already ⸺

134
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:49,534
What the landlord's wife won't keep quiet about

135
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:50,743
- (Torataro) Ah... - (Ichikawa) Yeah, yeah, yeah.

136
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:52,245
(Torataro) Is the landlord's wife strict?

137
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:53,621
strict! Yeah yeah tough

138
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:54,872
- (Torataro) Ah, it's tough - (Ichikawa) Yeah, it's tough.

139
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:55,873
-(Ichikawa) Yeah, yeah, it's tough! -(Torataro) Is it really that strict?

140
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:56,874
Yeah, amazing...

141
00:06:56,958 --> 00:07:00,169
(Torataro) Mr. Nishioka was transferred here on his own?

142
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:03,381
(Nishioka) Yes, my family is in Osaka.

143
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:05,800
Something about Mr. Goda in Room 5...

144
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:10,847
Well, did you take out the trash properly?

145
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:14,225
Despite appearances, I was sensible.

146
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:16,644
(Torataro) He followed his manners properly.

147
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:18,437
(sound of door closing)

148
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:21,149
(Knock) (Torataro) Mr. Mitsuyama What is your occupation?

149
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:23,901
(Mitsuyama) Well, it's called day trading.

150
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,444
(Torataro) Day trading...

151
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,822
Ah, plastic models are so cool!

152
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:29,574
(Mitsuyama) Ah, yes?

153
00:07:29,657 --> 00:07:31,659
(Torataro) Ah, regarding Mr. Goda in room 5⸺

154
00:07:31,742 --> 00:07:32,952
I would like to ask you.

155
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:36,330
- (Mitsuyama) Honestly, I'm not good at it - (Torataro) Ah...

156
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:39,333
But first, a little bit about the dog...

157
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:40,710
Does Mr. Ebihara keep it?

158
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:41,627
(Mitsuyama) Yes.

159
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:43,921
- (Mitsuyama) Actually, I'm allergic to dogs - (Torataro) Ah...

160
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:47,049
(Mitsuyama) It's pretty tough when the landlord takes it out.

161
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,595
...And when I told Mr. Goda about this, he complained to the landlord.

162
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:52,221
I see

163
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:54,390
(Torataro) It's Haruya Nasu, right?

164
00:07:54,473 --> 00:07:56,893
Excuse me, but what is your occupation...

165
00:07:58,519 --> 00:07:59,854
(Nasu) Personal trainer

166
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:03,983
That person, even though he looks scary, is quite kind.

167
00:08:04,066 --> 00:08:05,151
Mr. Ebihara's dog⸺

168
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:07,153
When you're left chained outside⸺

169
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:08,613
Are you playing?

170
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,907
Do you feel like a tsundere?

171
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:14,076
(Torataro) Ah, haha...

172
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,119
(sound of tapping on blackboard)

173
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:19,832
These are the residents of Goda's apartment.

174
00:08:21,417 --> 00:08:25,963
(Tatsumi) 1 2 3 4 and... 7

175
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:29,217
What? Huh?

176
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,093
Didn't you react blatantly just now?

177
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:33,054
No, um... it's nothing.

178
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:34,680
(Torataro) Among these five people⸺

179
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,933
Not a single person had a bad word to say about Goda.

180
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:38,476
Oh, unexpected

181
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,102
(Torataro) That's not all.

182
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:45,358
At the very end, I heard something very important from Mr. Yokouchi in Room 4.

183
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:48,528
 (Yokouchi) Mr. Goda has a dog⸺

184
00:08:48,611 --> 00:08:52,240
I don't think it's me who let him escape.

185
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,908
 (Torataro) Huh? What do you mean?

186
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:57,662
The landlord's dog is usually quiet⸺

187
00:08:58,746 --> 00:09:01,290
Only on that day did I hear the cry...

188
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:03,125
(dog barking)

189
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:04,961
(Footsteps) (Yokouchi) Ah!

190
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:08,965
I heard footsteps coming down the stairs outside.

191
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:10,716
When I went outside...

192
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,593
(Goda) Nothing in particular.

193
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:15,304
- (Ebihara) Get out of the way - (Goda) Tsk... Hey!

194
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:24,480
(Yokouchi) I think it was Mr. Goda who came down from the second floor.

195
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:27,191
Femme... Femme Fatale

196
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:29,485
...Not!

197
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:35,825
Goda was in his room on the second floor when the dog ran away.

198
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:40,663
Mr. Yokouchi, could you please testify in court?

199
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:44,750
Huh?

200
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,711
(Torataro) Mr. Yokouchi gave me the OK⸺

201
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:50,381
Call all the other residents for witness questioning.

202
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:53,509
I'm thinking of asking you to testify. Yeah.

203
00:09:53,592 --> 00:09:55,219
All five witnesses...

204
00:09:56,304 --> 00:10:00,182
-(Rie) Kotaro-sensei has an objection-(Korataro) Yes, something?

205
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:04,020
In the first place, letting the dog escape had nothing to do with the lease contract⸺

206
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:06,439
You're probably just emotionally strained by it.

207
00:10:06,522 --> 00:10:09,191
If so, let Mr. Goda apologize to the landlord⸺

208
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:10,943
You should ask for updates⸺

209
00:10:11,027 --> 00:10:12,194
I guess it's too early to talk

210
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,529
If that's the case⸺

211
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:16,157
Goda will admit that he let the dog escape, right?

212
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,701
But since Goda says he hasn't done it⸺

213
00:10:18,784 --> 00:10:21,203
I have to believe in Goda

214
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:25,875
I'm going to submit the witness application form.

215
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:34,133
Why are you making it so difficult for Mr. Kotaro?

216
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:37,303
(Sound of door opening and closing)

217
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:46,228
There is no doubt that the square seat is silver.

218
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:50,649
‪１ ２ ３ ４ ７

219
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:58,908
Ka... Kakugawarikoshikakegin?

220
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:04,205
(Kasumi) What's wrong, Torataro-sensei, you're not coming today?

221
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:05,539
(Tatsumi) This time it's Torataro-sensei⸺

222
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:09,794
Since I play alone, I'm the recorder, so to speak.

223
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:11,921
 (Tatsuo) Because I'm not with Tatsumi.

224
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:14,632
Is this something to be happy about?

225
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:17,968
(Kasumi) Could this be a witness? That's 5 people too

226
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:21,722
(Tatsumi) The defendant's attorney seemed reluctant⸺

227
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:23,891
On the condition that the interrogation time be shortened⸺

228
00:11:23,974 --> 00:11:26,102
It seems like I managed to get it recognized.

229
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:28,813
Mr. Kotaro did it unexpectedly.

230
00:11:28,896 --> 00:11:34,693
(Tatsumi) Hmm, the question is, in what order should you point out the witnesses?

231
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,153
Point to the witness?

232
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:43,744
(Tatsumi) It's a coincidence, but the room number of the witness this time⸺

233
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:48,249
It's the same as the line of foot that is indicated by the historical trace called Kakuwari Koshigake Gin.

234
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:51,544
As you know⸺

235
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:54,296
The opening pieces of Gin with a square replacement

236
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,841
(Kasumi) It's beautifully symmetrical.

237
00:11:56,924 --> 00:11:59,343
(Tatsumi) All 8 muscles except 5 muscles⸺

238
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:01,011
The pace of both the first and second players is⸺

239
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:03,472
Facing each other with a space in between⸺

240
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,141
The first move is from this set of pieces⸺

241
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:07,351
Which muscle step you hit first⸺

242
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,061
It will be the difference between victory and defeat.

243
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:10,479
The order of steps to set is⸺

244
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:13,065
There is a fixed path...

245
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:21,365
(Kasumi) You can win if you point in that order, right?

246
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:24,827
In that case, I need to tell Kotaro-sensei about it quickly.

247
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:28,497
The recorder cannot interfere in the game.

248
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,750
(Kasumi) The trial hasn't started yet, has it?

249
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:35,045
Before the match, study your opponent's moves with your fellow members of the study group⸺

250
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:38,841
I don't think it's worth it to give advice.

251
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:41,719
Then it might be possible

252
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:47,057
I'll go for a while

253
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:50,394
Huh? Huh? At this hour?

254
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:52,354
-(Kasumi) Be careful.-(Tatsumi) Yeah.

255
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,023
(sigh)

256
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:58,402
After all, maybe it won't work unless those two are together.

257
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,280
(Tatsuo) Hmm...

258
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:04,325
Huh...

259
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:14,251
“Fukuo Goda”? I've seen it somewhere...

260
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:23,177
(door chime)

261
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:24,303
(Torataro) Yeah?

262
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:29,058
Huh?

263
00:13:35,689 --> 00:13:37,316
This is...

264
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:40,986
It's a blocker. Please watch it after today's game is over.

265
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:45,115
Ahhh...

266
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:58,337
Ah, already!

267
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:03,092
 Huh?

268
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:07,304
Haa... Why is it Shogi again?

269
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,396
Witness order?

270
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:20,276
surely⸺

271
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:23,404
Maybe it's not bad

272
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:32,538
(Vibrator on mobile phone) (Torataro) Hey... Hey, call me.

273
00:14:32,621 --> 00:14:34,874
- (Torataro) Phone, I'm coming - (Goda) Ah? Hey

274
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,552
Landlord

275
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:54,018
(Rie) Huh? 4 2 1 7 3?

276
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:57,146
Ideally, you should testify in that order.

277
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:01,567
Well, first of all, Mr. Yokouchi in Room 4⸺

278
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,694
Goda says he hasn't let the dog escape.

279
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:05,321
give important testimony

280
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,948
Next, to Mr. Nishioka in Room 2⸺

281
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:10,993
Mr. Goda follows good manners when taking out the trash.

282
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:14,913
Mr. Ichikawa in Room 1 is not in arrears with his rent.

283
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:18,667
Mr. Nasu in Room 7 said that Mr. Goda likes dogs.

284
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:21,503
Eh~ For Mr. Mitsuyama in room 3⸺

285
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:24,256
Mr. Goda complained to the landlord

286
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:28,093
If you take steps in that order, you will definitely win.

287
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:31,221
It seems far-fetched, but it's not bad, right?

288
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:35,476
It's tough~ Mr. Yokouchi from room 4 will be late.

289
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:37,645
-(Torataro) Hey... -(Tatsumi) Ah...

290
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:42,650
(Torataro) Hey Yokouchi-san, where are you now?

291
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:46,820
Ah, oh... oops... please calm down.

292
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:49,073
It's okay, yes

293
00:15:49,156 --> 00:15:52,701
10 minutes? Understood yes

294
00:15:53,202 --> 00:15:54,703
What happened?

295
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:58,040
Mr. Yokouchi: For some reason, the door to my room won't open.

296
00:15:58,123 --> 00:15:59,833
It's like I'm trapped

297
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:02,795
-(Torataro) I'll be 10 minutes late.-(Rie) 10 minutes...

298
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:05,047
The trial is about to begin.

299
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:07,174
Ah, okay, then... I'll take you right away when you come.

300
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:08,634
Kotaro Sensei, go back to court.

301
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:10,094
Understood yes

302
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:23,107
(Presiding Judge) Are all the witnesses representing the plaintiff available?

303
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:26,819
No, one person was late.

304
00:16:26,902 --> 00:16:28,320
Interrogation time is limited

305
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,697
please wait a moment

306
00:16:35,577 --> 00:16:38,038
At first, I want someone who is good at talking.

307
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:42,418
(Secretary) Please stand up.

308
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:50,175
(Ichikawa) “Speak the truth according to your oath of conscience⸺”

309
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:54,471
“I promise not to hide anything or lie.”

310
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:57,766
No, no, no, you can't attack from the beginning!

311
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:00,936
- (Presiding Judge) The audience seats must be quiet - (Tatsumi) I'm sorry.

312
00:17:01,019 --> 00:17:02,479
(Secretary) Please take a seat.

313
00:17:03,063 --> 00:17:05,899
(Torataro) Plaintiff's attorney Fuda asks a question.

314
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:10,404
The witness seems to be familiar with the relationships between people in the apartment.

315
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:14,032
Please tell us what you know about the plaintiff, Mr. Goda.

316
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:19,371
Goda-san, at first glance, he's scary but manly.

317
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:23,584
I forgot to mention it the other day, but it was the same with Mr. Nishioka.

318
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,962
Yeah? Who is Mr. Nishioka in Room 2?

319
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,506
(Ichikawa) Yes, Mr. Nishioka, actually⸺

320
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:32,926
Looks like he's having fun with Mr. Yokouchi in Room 4.

321
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:39,516
But Mr. Nishioka, his wife and children are in Osaka, right?

322
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:42,394
When I told Goda-san about it...

323
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:45,230
(Goda) I would feel bad if I was accused of having an affair.

324
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:48,692
(Ichikawa) I told Mr. Nishioka that I couldn't tolerate infidelity.

325
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:50,527
It's a man

326
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:54,364
(Presiding judge) Witnesses should not talk about anything unrelated to the trial.

327
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:56,408
-(Ichikawa) Yeah-(Torataro) Ah, uh...

328
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:58,911
- (Ichikawa) Yeah, yeah - (Torataro) Mr. Ichikawa, that's enough.

329
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,037
(Ichikawa) Is that so? Yes, yes.

330
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,498
(Tatsumi) The order in which to attack Ayumu with Kakuwagi Gin is ⸺

331
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:06,335
If you don't point them in the correct order, something terrible will happen.

332
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:10,589
What is it? That person

333
00:18:11,673 --> 00:18:14,593
Among them, there is one thing that you should never attack first.

334
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:17,971
If you hit 15 steps when you should hit 45 steps, the second step is the same step.

335
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:20,140
(Presiding Judge) What about the defendant's cross-examination?

336
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:22,059
(Yoshimura) Especially... Huh...

337
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:24,812
I... Excuse me, nothing in particular.

338
00:18:25,562 --> 00:18:28,649
(Presiding judge) Plaintiff's representative: The following witnesses:

339
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:30,609
yes

340
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:36,031
Now, once again, witness Norie Yokouchi.

341
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,992
The witness was when Ebihara's dog ran away...

342
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:42,538
I won't say anything. I refuse to testify.

343
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,081
But during this time...

344
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:48,210
I agreed to testify on behalf of Mr. Goda.

345
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:51,713
But why do we have to reveal everything about that person?

346
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:54,716
 (Tatsumi) With a silver seat instead of a horn⸺

347
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,636
After making a mistake in the order of the five steps⸺

348
00:18:57,719 --> 00:19:00,889
Even if I take two or four steps to get back on track...

349
00:19:01,765 --> 00:19:05,978
As a witness, Mr. Goda is a resident of Yaguraso⸺

350
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:07,646
Observe proper manners when taking out trash...

351
00:19:07,729 --> 00:19:08,605
What are manners!

352
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:12,401
Goda's guy pretends to be a righteous man and sticks his nose into other people's affairs!

353
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:15,946
You caught my part! It's definitely an assault, right?

354
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:18,866
(Torataro) Already... Already! no thanks

355
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:22,327
- (Torataro) That's it - (Tatsumi) The draw is 24 Dogin.

356
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,748
Mr. Goda was petting the dog.

357
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:29,918
That's right, I was cute, unexpectedly, because I was cute⸺

358
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:33,297
Maybe he left it in a cage and felt sorry for him so he let him go.

359
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,215
That's enough!

360
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:40,888
Still sticking to the fixed path, taking the first 75 steps and taking the second step.

361
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:43,765
(Torataro) Something about Mr. Goda?

362
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:46,977
(Tatsumi) Even if I struggled and managed to take 4 steps...

363
00:19:49,062 --> 00:19:53,025
Actually, I heard about it through rumors⸺

364
00:19:53,650 --> 00:19:58,238
Goda-san, you've been arrested for causing bodily harm before...

365
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,698
-(Torataro) Huh! ? -(Goda) Hey!

366
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:00,699
It doesn't matter! That kind of thing

367
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,409
(Presiding judge) Plaintiff should be quiet.

368
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:08,040
Questions are... That's all.

369
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:12,669
I was told that I was 17 steps behind.

370
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:17,507
Even if I panicked and attacked with 7 and 4 steps, I was only 28 on the back...

371
00:20:19,426 --> 00:20:24,681
The first player loses his own rook and is forced to struggle.

372
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:27,726
It looks like Torataro-sensei is completely stuck.

373
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:42,199
Kotaro, are you trying to make fun of me?

374
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:45,160
More than that⸺

375
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:49,373
Is it true that you have been arrested?

376
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:52,584
Tsk...what is that?

377
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:54,920
why didn't you tell me

378
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:57,422
It's not really something to talk about.

379
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:03,929
You said you didn't let the dog escape.

380
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:08,517
If that's the case, why were you looking into the landlord's room in the first place?

381
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:12,688
-(Yoshimura) It was completely self-destructive.-(Ebihara) Yeah.

382
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:18,110
It probably doesn't matter to Kotaro.

383
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:20,028
It doesn't matter!

384
00:21:21,196 --> 00:21:23,699
What if the client is hiding something?

385
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:27,411
Even if you can win a lawsuit, you might not win, right?

386
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:28,662
Huh?

387
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,873
I guess that's the one who told you to go to court.

388
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:34,084
But you let me go through this.

389
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:38,630
I thought friend would do something about it.

390
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:41,633
I was stupid!

391
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:08,410
(Sound of door opening and closing)

392
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:11,580
(Staff) Welcome.

393
00:22:12,330 --> 00:22:14,458
(Tatsumi) Can I sit next to you?

394
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:17,294
(Torataro) Huh?

395
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:20,297
Ah, I asked Rie-san.

396
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:23,967
Mr. Kotaro lost the lawsuit⸺

397
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:26,386
When you lose a crushing settlement negotiation⸺

398
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:28,346
Eating two gyoza at this restaurant⸺

399
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:30,891
It's a small way to relieve stress.

400
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:39,441
Your explanation may be too specific

401
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:42,611
- (Torataro) Huh... - (Staff) Would you like something to drink?

402
00:22:42,694 --> 00:22:45,906
-(Tatsumi) Oh, I have the same thing too.-(Salesperson) Aiyo.

403
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:49,993
(Torataro's sigh)

404
00:22:54,956 --> 00:22:55,957
(Tatsumi) Goda-san⸺

405
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:59,461
He referred to Torataro-sensei as a friend.

406
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:04,508
What kind of relationship did you have?

407
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:13,350
To him⸺

408
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:19,231
As a lawyer, I have to protect it until the end⸺

409
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:22,025
I learned something like a flag.

410
00:23:22,943 --> 00:23:25,278
A flag that must be protected?

411
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:32,077
During the final exam of my third year of junior high school when I was in the same class as that guy⸺

412
00:23:33,453 --> 00:23:37,124
I was suspected of cheating.

413
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:38,583
(Tatsumi) Huh? Did Kotaro-sensei cheat?

414
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,544
- (Torataro) Because I didn't - (Tatsumi) Ah, ah...

415
00:23:41,837 --> 00:23:42,671
Yeah?

416
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:45,257
(sigh)

417
00:23:47,342 --> 00:23:51,555
(Student) This is clear evidence of cheating, right?

418
00:23:51,638 --> 00:23:54,224
(Toratarō, a junior high school student) No! I just forgot to put it in my bag...

419
00:23:54,307 --> 00:23:57,978
(Student) Criminals always tell you not to do it.

420
00:23:58,061 --> 00:23:58,895
laughter)

421
00:23:58,979 --> 00:24:01,690
(Student) No wonder I got good grades.

422
00:24:02,274 --> 00:24:04,985
(Junior high school student Goda) Don't do it, Torataro.

423
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:08,321
There's no way this guy has that kind of courage.

424
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:14,077
(Torataro) Goda sat right behind me throughout the test.

425
00:24:14,161 --> 00:24:16,454
Trying to see my answer⸺

426
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:21,793
I haven't even touched the vocabulary book⸺

427
00:24:21,877 --> 00:24:23,753
He testified.

428
00:24:24,421 --> 00:24:28,133
Thanks to you, the commotion subsided, but Goda took his place⸺

429
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:31,219
I got 0 points as a punishment for cheating.

430
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:34,389
(Toratarō, a junior high school student) Why did you go that far for me...

431
00:24:35,056 --> 00:24:36,308
Torataro

432
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:39,478
I almost said I did it.

433
00:24:39,561 --> 00:24:42,606
Huh? ah…

434
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:47,319
When I say I did something I shouldn't have done⸺

435
00:24:47,402 --> 00:24:49,196
I'll be a loser all my life

436
00:24:53,366 --> 00:24:55,452
(Torataro) You did something you hadn't done⸺

437
00:24:55,535 --> 00:24:57,496
Never say it

438
00:24:57,996 --> 00:24:59,581
no matter what

439
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:04,836
That's why when Goda asked me for help⸺

440
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,964
If he says he didn't do it, then he didn't do it.

441
00:25:09,257 --> 00:25:12,219
I decided that I absolutely believed it.

442
00:25:14,054 --> 00:25:14,888
(Staff) Yes, please wait.

443
00:25:14,971 --> 00:25:17,224
(Tatsumi) Ah... Thank you.

444
00:25:22,062 --> 00:25:23,438
But...

445
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:28,610
When I heard that you had been arrested⸺

446
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:33,448
I suddenly lost my confidence

447
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:38,036
We haven't seen each other for almost 15 years since we graduated⸺

448
00:25:39,746 --> 00:25:43,792
This guy isn't the Goda I know⸺

449
00:25:45,168 --> 00:25:48,338
Maybe he really let the dog escape?

450
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:50,048
Like that⸺

451
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:53,551
I don't like myself starting to doubt myself

452
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:09,985
- (Tatsumi) Um... I'm sorry, already - (Torataro) Hahahaha...

453
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:13,655
Huh... I wonder if one beer will do this?

454
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:16,616
Haa... aaa... haa...

455
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:19,202
(Entrance chime) (Sound of door opening)

456
00:26:19,911 --> 00:26:22,831
Hahahaha... ah dad...

457
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:26,501
(Tatsuo) I wonder how close they are to each other in the middle of the night like this...

458
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:28,086
There are so many… so many… so many things.

459
00:26:28,169 --> 00:26:29,170
various! ? Huh?

460
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:31,631
What kind of color is that “color”?

461
00:26:31,715 --> 00:26:35,093
-(Kasumi) Tatsuo-san, what happened? -(Torataro) Ah, ah... Mom.

462
00:26:35,176 --> 00:26:38,471
Ah... for now, please put down Ryumi-san.

463
00:26:38,555 --> 00:26:39,931
- (Kasumi) Yes, uhhh... yes - (Tatsuo) “Tatsumi-san”?

464
00:26:40,015 --> 00:26:40,849
(Torataro) No.

465
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:45,770
(sound of tapping on table)

466
00:26:46,563 --> 00:26:50,233
I feel like I'm being sentenced somehow.

467
00:26:50,317 --> 00:26:53,945
Guilty of carrying him home on his back!

468
00:26:54,029 --> 00:26:57,157
No, but in this case, both of us have agreed...

469
00:26:57,240 --> 00:27:01,661
agreement? I never thought it would be more than a piggy back ride...

470
00:27:01,745 --> 00:27:03,705
No, no, no... that's a misunderstanding.

471
00:27:03,788 --> 00:27:05,749
Mr. Tatsuo, please be careful.

472
00:27:05,832 --> 00:27:08,668
You sent me Ryumi, so I have to thank you.

473
00:27:08,752 --> 00:27:13,381
No... that's kind of... Yes, I'm really sorry. Thank you.

474
00:27:14,758 --> 00:27:16,634
(Sigh) (Tapping on shoulder)

475
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,554
Huh?

476
00:27:20,764 --> 00:27:22,057
This is...

477
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:25,602
A copy of the documents from this trial...

478
00:27:26,144 --> 00:27:29,731
Ryumi: Because I want to be of help to Torataro-sensei⸺

479
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:31,107
Take it home⸺

480
00:27:31,191 --> 00:27:34,027
I've been wondering if there's a better way.

481
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:39,199
The plaintiff is your classmate?

482
00:27:39,741 --> 00:27:43,244
Yes, my name is Fukuo Goda, and I went to middle school...

483
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:44,412
(Tatsuo) Yes.

484
00:27:45,538 --> 00:27:47,582
I remembered that name

485
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:52,921
He was a defendant I was in charge of when I was in the criminal department...

486
00:27:53,004 --> 00:27:54,297
Huh?

487
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:58,343
(Tatsumi) Sorry...

488
00:28:03,098 --> 00:28:06,810
(Torataro) About the injury incident caused by Yube Goda⸺

489
00:28:06,893 --> 00:28:08,853
I heard it from Ryumi-sensei's father.

490
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:11,314
While I was sound asleep...

491
00:28:11,398 --> 00:28:15,026
(Torataro) Five years ago, Goda was working as a debt collector.

492
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:18,822
Arrested and prosecuted for injuring a senior employee there

493
00:28:18,905 --> 00:28:23,743
The sentence is one year in prison, but the sentence is suspended.

494
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:28,081
Actually, the victim's employee was a terrible person⸺

495
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:33,086
It's a good thing that young female customers who can't pay their debts can't resist⸺

496
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:36,005
Goda couldn't bear to see me forcing myself into a relationship...

497
00:28:36,089 --> 00:28:40,135
(Goda) Senpai, hey... stop it, it's too much.

498
00:28:40,218 --> 00:28:43,555
(Male) Goda, what are you planning on doing?

499
00:28:43,638 --> 00:28:45,348
- (Goda) Huh... wait... - (Male) Hey!

500
00:28:45,432 --> 00:28:48,977
(Goda) Please stop... Ah... (Falling sound)

501
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:51,271
(woman screams)

502
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:55,024
So, is that a charge of assault?

503
00:28:55,108 --> 00:28:58,278
(Torataro) The defense attorney at the time claimed self-defense.

504
00:28:59,195 --> 00:29:01,072
The opponent's injuries were also serious⸺

505
00:29:01,156 --> 00:29:04,242
My father, who was the presiding judge, also thought about it a lot.

506
00:29:04,325 --> 00:29:06,953
I was sentenced to a suspended sentence.

507
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:09,664
I thought he had clearly lost his temper and acted violently.

508
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:13,710
I am Goda⸺

509
00:29:15,211 --> 00:29:17,172
Just because I'm angry⸺

510
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:21,759
I want to believe that he's not the kind of guy who would let the landlord's dog run away.

511
00:29:30,226 --> 00:29:34,564
The trial turned into a pretty bad situation.

512
00:29:35,482 --> 00:29:39,027
But I want to try a little harder.

513
00:29:39,819 --> 00:29:43,615
For that, we need the power of two people.

514
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:46,034
Please help me!

515
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:49,245
Ah, that's enough... that's enough.

516
00:29:49,329 --> 00:29:51,247
I understand.

517
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:54,000
I was also at fault for judging people by their appearance.

518
00:29:54,083 --> 00:29:56,211
The game isn't over yet.

519
00:29:58,546 --> 00:30:00,048
I also refer to

520
00:30:00,131 --> 00:30:03,092
If you decide to do that, how do you plan to counterattack?

521
00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:09,724
First, I'll go to Yagura-so again and listen to the story.

522
00:30:10,642 --> 00:30:13,144
(Ebihara) Why are you talking about dogs now?

523
00:30:13,228 --> 00:30:16,439
(Tatsumi) Is Kotaro-kun usually in here?

524
00:30:16,523 --> 00:30:20,902
Ah, whenever I can't take care of myself, I'm always here

525
00:30:22,403 --> 00:30:25,323
Oh... your wife won't be taken care of?

526
00:30:25,406 --> 00:30:28,368
Yeah, well, I do love her, though⸺

527
00:30:28,451 --> 00:30:31,037
Food, toilet, etc.

528
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:36,167
Leave all the troublesome care to me, everything to me

529
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:37,710
Ah ah...

530
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:49,430
(Torataro) Huh? Isn't this a blood stain?

531
00:30:49,514 --> 00:30:51,808
- (Ebihara) Huh? - (Torataro) Here...

532
00:30:52,642 --> 00:30:55,103
 (Ebihara) Oh... what? this

533
00:30:59,899 --> 00:31:01,317
(Tatsumi) As expected, this is the match⸺

534
00:31:01,401 --> 00:31:04,863
There is no doubt that the dog is a key piece.

535
00:31:04,946 --> 00:31:07,031
Eh, but dogs don't have pieces, right?

536
00:31:08,116 --> 00:31:11,160
-(Tatsumi) There is that.-(Torataro) Seriously?

537
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:14,622
Makadai Shogi The shogi that is said to be the root of modern shogi is⸺

538
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:18,167
Battle with 50 types of pieces using a board larger than normal.

539
00:31:18,251 --> 00:31:20,086
Among them is a piece called Komainu.

540
00:31:20,169 --> 00:31:21,462
Proceed in all 8 directions⸺

541
00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:23,798
It is said that you can even capture the opponent's pieces that are ahead of you⸺

542
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:26,092
It's a very high spec piece.

543
00:31:26,175 --> 00:31:27,218
(Torataro) Yeah...

544
00:31:28,469 --> 00:31:31,389
That poop has nothing to do with this trial, right?

545
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:40,064
(Tatsumi) Um... That's Kie Yokouchi's room, isn't it?

546
00:31:40,148 --> 00:31:41,316
(Torataro) Yeah.

547
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:49,365
He said he was late for the trial because the door wouldn't open.

548
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:54,287
(Tatsumi) Um... I'm sorry, did something happen?

549
00:31:54,370 --> 00:31:55,538
(Businessman) Someone somewhere⸺

550
00:31:55,622 --> 00:31:59,250
It looks like they poured some glue or something into the keyhole.

551
00:31:59,876 --> 00:32:04,380
Because of that, I was late for Mr. Yokouchi's trial.

552
00:32:05,214 --> 00:32:06,799
I'm sorry

553
00:32:06,883 --> 00:32:09,218
Testifying in court is a rare experience.

554
00:32:09,302 --> 00:32:11,220
A switch was turned on in a strange place

555
00:32:11,304 --> 00:32:15,266
Thanks to that testimony, I'm on the verge of giving up.

556
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:19,979
I don't want to apologize, but I'll tell you some special information.

557
00:32:20,063 --> 00:32:21,230
What? What?

558
00:32:21,314 --> 00:32:23,566
(Ichikawa) It's okay, it's okay... Hurry, hurry, hey...

559
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:27,195
Actually, the landlord is Mr. Ebihara⸺

560
00:32:27,278 --> 00:32:30,490
Apparently I won 1 million yen in the lottery.

561
00:32:30,573 --> 00:32:31,950
By lottery?

562
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:34,285
But that 1 million yen⸺

563
00:32:34,369 --> 00:32:37,580
It seems like he kept it a secret from his wife and hid it.

564
00:32:37,664 --> 00:32:40,667
Huh? Eh, then there's 1 million yen in your room?

565
00:32:40,750 --> 00:32:42,001
- (Ichikawa) Yes, yes, yes, yes - (Torataro) Yes?

566
00:32:42,085 --> 00:32:43,252
(Tatsumi) That’s it⸺

567
00:32:43,336 --> 00:32:45,672
Do you know any other residents?

568
00:32:45,755 --> 00:32:48,466
Since the landlord's wife is a hot topic, I told everyone.

569
00:32:48,549 --> 00:32:50,927
laughter)

570
00:32:51,010 --> 00:32:52,679
By any chance...

571
00:33:18,538 --> 00:33:20,623
(Ebihara) You did something outrageous, give it back quickly!

572
00:33:20,707 --> 00:33:23,376
(Businessman) Looks like they poured some glue or something into the keyhole.

573
00:33:23,459 --> 00:33:24,544
(Torataro) Isn't this a blood stain?

574
00:33:24,627 --> 00:33:26,379
(Ichikawa) It seems like he hid that 1 million yen.

575
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:32,969
(Tatsumi) This one game...

576
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:38,975
It wasn't the dog that disappeared...

577
00:33:45,815 --> 00:33:47,400
(Rie) Goda's father⸺

578
00:33:47,483 --> 00:33:50,361
He passed away from a myocardial infarction five years ago.

579
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:54,282
That was around the time of the injury incident.

580
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:57,785
Maybe he moved to Yagura-so after this.

581
00:34:02,915 --> 00:34:05,543
Yeah? Did you find any help?

582
00:34:06,335 --> 00:34:11,591
I'm going to win this game, and I know everything about the culprit.

583
00:34:11,674 --> 00:34:12,717
Ahhh...

584
00:34:13,968 --> 00:34:16,262
- (Torataro) It's supposed to be a civil trial, but - (Tatsumi) Mr. Torataro.

585
00:34:16,345 --> 00:34:20,767
Could you please let me know your next move?

586
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:34,530
ah? Is it a coming-of-age ceremony?

587
00:34:54,675 --> 00:34:57,428
Suddenly, what do you mean by consultations outside of litigation?

588
00:34:57,512 --> 00:35:02,892
This time, there are hidden pieces that don't appear in normal shogi.

589
00:35:03,392 --> 00:35:05,311
It turned into a difficult game.

590
00:35:07,897 --> 00:35:09,899
Can you say it a little more understandably?

591
00:35:09,982 --> 00:35:10,858
- (Tatsumi) Yes - (Torataro) Yeah.

592
00:35:12,610 --> 00:35:16,405
Mr. Ebihara won 1 million yen in the lottery⸺

593
00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:18,991
You were hiding it in Kotaro-kun's cage, right?

594
00:35:19,575 --> 00:35:20,660
How do you know!

595
00:35:20,743 --> 00:35:23,955
Even though his wife Suzuko loves dogs⸺

596
00:35:24,038 --> 00:35:27,542
I left all the care of Kotaro-kun to Ebihara-san.

597
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:31,671
That's why there's something inside the cage that Suzuko doesn't touch.

598
00:35:31,754 --> 00:35:33,464
perfect hiding place

599
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:38,261
(Torataro) I see.

600
00:35:38,761 --> 00:35:41,597
Because I mistakenly thought Goda had stolen the money⸺

601
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:42,849
Something like that...

602
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:43,850
Return it quickly!

603
00:35:43,933 --> 00:35:47,228
(Tatsumi) It's unnatural to say "give back the dog that ran away"⸺

604
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:49,272
I was curious from the beginning

605
00:35:49,939 --> 00:35:52,275
Wait, I'm not taking any money!

606
00:35:52,358 --> 00:35:54,152
So who took it?

607
00:35:55,611 --> 00:36:00,533
The key to this game was Ayumu's five cards from the beginning.

608
00:36:02,451 --> 00:36:04,912
Judging from the situation, there are five possible suspects⸺

609
00:36:05,496 --> 00:36:11,836
1 2 3 4 someone among the 7 steps

610
00:36:16,382 --> 00:36:19,802
There are two conditions to narrow down the culprit.

611
00:36:19,886 --> 00:36:20,970
First one

612
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:22,138
(dog barking)

613
00:36:22,221 --> 00:36:25,141
(Tatsumi) The culprit had 1 million yen hidden in the cage⸺

614
00:36:25,224 --> 00:36:26,517
When I tried to steal it...

615
00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:27,894
(squeak) (chewing sound)

616
00:36:28,644 --> 00:36:32,815
Kotaro-kun bit my hand and it started bleeding.

617
00:36:33,566 --> 00:36:37,820
Second, the culprit who tried to pin the blame on Goda was⸺

618
00:36:37,904 --> 00:36:42,283
I heard that Mr. Yokouchi would give testimony denying that.

619
00:36:42,366 --> 00:36:45,995
(Torataro) Mr. Goda was in his room on the second floor when the dog ran away.

620
00:36:46,078 --> 00:36:48,164
Could you testify in court?

621
00:36:48,247 --> 00:36:52,126
(Tatsumi) That's why I decided to lock Mr. Yokouchi in the room on the day of the trial.

622
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,879
using instant adhesive

623
00:36:54,962 --> 00:36:59,842
I have a dog bite wound and I usually use superglue.

624
00:36:59,926 --> 00:37:02,219
The pieces that meet that condition are...

625
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:07,767
3 steps

626
00:37:09,352 --> 00:37:11,479
I'm the culprit who let the dog escape.

627
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:20,780
You know why I came, right?

628
00:37:21,948 --> 00:37:23,866
(Tatsumi) Scar on left hand⸺

629
00:37:23,950 --> 00:37:26,202
Isn't that the wound from Kotaro-kun's bite?

630
00:37:26,285 --> 00:37:30,498
The glue I used for the keyhole in Yokouchi's room is also there.

631
00:37:30,581 --> 00:37:32,792
-(Mitsuyama) Ah, no, this is... -(Tatsumi) It's already full.

632
00:37:33,793 --> 00:37:35,419
Please concede

633
00:37:41,509 --> 00:37:43,427
Failed day trading⸺

634
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:46,806
My debt has increased to the point where I can't pay it back.

635
00:37:49,850 --> 00:37:51,268
sorry!

636
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:53,437
Hmph!

637
00:37:57,108 --> 00:38:00,277
(Goda) Is it okay? Police, don't push me

638
00:38:01,153 --> 00:38:03,364
(Ebihara) I got the money back.

639
00:38:03,864 --> 00:38:06,701
However, I will ask you to leave.

640
00:38:07,743 --> 00:38:10,413
I guess your attitude is too different from when I was there.

641
00:38:11,038 --> 00:38:14,000
Okay? In the first place, are you⸺

642
00:38:14,083 --> 00:38:16,210
Peek into my room from time to time⸺

643
00:38:16,293 --> 00:38:19,672
I probably went inside the room that day too.

644
00:38:20,798 --> 00:38:22,717
(Torataro) I know the reason.

645
00:38:24,051 --> 00:38:25,886
Probably Goda that day.

646
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:30,016
I heard the sound of Kotaro running outside while crying.

647
00:38:30,599 --> 00:38:33,352
I ran down the stairs and headed to Ebihara-san's room.

648
00:38:34,186 --> 00:38:35,354
The reason is...

649
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:37,857
(Goda) Landlord! Are you okay? ?

650
00:38:37,940 --> 00:38:39,025
(Torataro) In Ebihara-san's body⸺

651
00:38:39,108 --> 00:38:41,986
It was because I was worried that something might have happened.

652
00:38:42,069 --> 00:38:44,989
Huh? Why is this guy talking about me?

653
00:38:45,072 --> 00:38:47,324
Last time I visited you, you were swallowing medicine.

654
00:38:47,908 --> 00:38:50,077
Do you have any chronic illness?

655
00:38:50,161 --> 00:38:50,995
(Ebihara) Oh

656
00:38:51,078 --> 00:38:52,955
Just take a break from your heart

657
00:38:54,665 --> 00:38:58,836
(Torataro) Actually, Goda's father also has a heart disease...

658
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:03,257
Isn't that so?

659
00:39:06,969 --> 00:39:08,012
(clicks tongue)

660
00:39:10,431 --> 00:39:11,807
5 years ago⸺

661
00:39:12,683 --> 00:39:16,270
I made a fool of myself at work and collapsed before I could even go home.

662
00:39:19,106 --> 00:39:21,192
He just passed away

663
00:39:24,779 --> 00:39:27,698
I heard that Mr. Ebihara also has a heart disease⸺

664
00:39:28,532 --> 00:39:30,284
I was always worried about it.

665
00:39:30,367 --> 00:39:33,496
It's not like that though.

666
00:39:35,081 --> 00:39:37,375
(Torataro) Goda didn't want to leave his apartment.

667
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:40,294
I think it was because I was worried about Ebihara-san.

668
00:39:44,423 --> 00:39:46,926
Why are you worrying about other people?

669
00:39:50,679 --> 00:39:55,101
Don't worry, I won't tell you to leave.

670
00:39:58,896 --> 00:39:59,939
Huh...

671
00:40:04,443 --> 00:40:06,946
(Bicycle brake sound)

672
00:40:07,029 --> 00:40:11,033
(Suzuko) Hey, I just got a call from the ward office.

673
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:13,244
Kotaro-chan was found.

674
00:40:13,327 --> 00:40:16,247
- (Goda) Are you serious? -(Suzuko) Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh…

675
00:40:16,330 --> 00:40:17,748
Oh, come pick me up at the protection center.

676
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:20,084
(Ebihara) Ah... Yeah, yeah, I understand.

677
00:40:21,460 --> 00:40:23,712
(Goda) Thank you, Torataro

678
00:40:24,964 --> 00:40:26,006
no

679
00:40:27,174 --> 00:40:30,511
I was just working as a lawyer.

680
00:40:30,594 --> 00:40:32,346
-(Goda) It's different.-(Korataro) Yeah?

681
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:36,892
You would have believed in me until the end.

682
00:40:39,520 --> 00:40:40,729
Huh...

683
00:40:42,064 --> 00:40:45,109
If you say you did something you've never done before⸺

684
00:40:45,192 --> 00:40:47,528
Because I'll be a loser all my life

685
00:40:47,611 --> 00:40:48,821
(sound of tapping on the shoulder)

686
00:40:49,655 --> 00:40:51,866
(Junior high school student Goda) When I said I did something I shouldn't have done⸺

687
00:40:51,949 --> 00:40:53,325
Because I'll be a loser all my life

688
00:40:53,409 --> 00:40:54,535
(Torataro) Huh...

689
00:40:54,702 --> 00:40:56,704
♪～

690
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:02,543
I'm glad you're the one after all

691
00:41:02,626 --> 00:41:05,212
Whoa... it hurts haha...

692
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:08,799
(Torataro/Goda) Hey, hey, hey...

693
00:41:08,883 --> 00:41:11,135
(Torataro) Oh... Hey, hey!

694
00:41:11,218 --> 00:41:12,636
laughter)

695
00:41:14,972 --> 00:41:16,307
 (sound pointing to piece)

696
00:41:16,390 --> 00:41:18,809
(Torataro) After all, we're going to have a battle of impressions.

697
00:41:18,893 --> 00:41:20,269
(Tatsumi) It makes me think about a lot of things⸺

698
00:41:20,352 --> 00:41:22,104
It was one game.

699
00:41:24,690 --> 00:41:25,524
 (sound pointing to piece)

700
00:41:26,358 --> 00:41:28,569
I'm glad Ryumi-sensei is here.

701
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:33,073
I ignored the flow of moves⸺

702
00:41:33,157 --> 00:41:35,117
It sounds like a sudden move, but

703
00:41:35,201 --> 00:41:36,243
 (sound pointing to piece)

704
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:39,038
I was determined to do it alone⸺

705
00:41:40,539 --> 00:41:42,166
Mr. Ryumi⸺

706
00:41:42,875 --> 00:41:44,668
I can't believe you're thinking so hard.

707
00:41:44,752 --> 00:41:46,170
Because I didn't notice

708
00:41:47,713 --> 00:41:50,299
I read the game's moves⸺

709
00:41:50,382 --> 00:41:52,384
It's like a habit.

710
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:56,764
But it helped

711
00:41:59,141 --> 00:42:00,684
Thank you very much

712
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:10,110
Ah... yes

713
00:42:17,076 --> 00:42:19,495
(Tatsumi) Personally, I was jealous.

714
00:42:20,871 --> 00:42:23,499
 (Torataro) Yeah? Are you jealous?

715
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:27,211
(Tatsumi) To Torataro-sensei⸺

716
00:42:27,294 --> 00:42:30,881
I have a friend like Goda-san.

717
00:42:30,965 --> 00:42:32,967
～♪

718
00:42:33,133 --> 00:42:34,343
No, but⸺

719
00:42:34,927 --> 00:42:36,262
Even for Tatsumi-sensei⸺

720
00:42:36,345 --> 00:42:37,554
You have some friends, right?

721
00:42:37,638 --> 00:42:39,890
Huh...I'm a shogi player⸺

722
00:42:39,974 --> 00:42:42,393
Plus, it was a life of “Rokupo Zensho”

723
00:42:42,977 --> 00:42:46,021
That might be amazing.

724
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:52,361
But I had one best friend.

725
00:42:59,243 --> 00:43:00,911
But I am⸺

726
00:43:02,663 --> 00:43:04,790
I lost that person

727
00:43:08,377 --> 00:43:09,962
At shogi

728
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:17,344
 (sound pointing to piece)

729
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:19,680
What about this rice cake?

730
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:20,681
(Torataro) License agreement⸺

731
00:43:20,764 --> 00:43:21,599
Bound...

